properties.headline: Rip Current Statement issued January 28 at 9:22AM EST until January 28 at 10:00PM EST by NWS Miami FL
properties.description:
* WHAT...Dangerous rip currents.

* WHERE...Northern Coastal Palm Beach County.

* WHEN...Through this evening.

* IMPACTS...Rip currents can sweep even the best swimmers away
from shore into deeper water.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...High Rip Current Risk for Northern Coastal
Palm Beach County and Moderate Rip Current Risk for Southern
Coastal Palm Beach County.
properties.instruction:
Swim near a lifeguard. If caught in a rip current, relax and
float. Don't swim against the current. If able, swim in a
direction following the shoreline. If unable to escape, face the
shore and call or wave for help.

NWSheadline: HIGH RIP CURRENT RISK IN EFFECT THROUGH THIS EVENING
